==English==

===Etymology===
A saints' name from the {{etyl|la|en}} gens name {{m|la|Ignatius}}, {{m|la|Egnatius}}, of uncertain meaning, by [[folk etymology]] associated with Latin {{m|la|ignis||fire}}. It might be related to Ancient Greek {{l|grc|ἴγνης||indigene}}, {{m|grc|ἴγνητος}}, from {{m|grc|*ἔν-γνη-τες}}, formed from {{m|grc|έν}} + {{der|la|ine-pro|*ǵenh₁-|t=to give birth, produce}}, also seen in {{m|grc|γίγνομαι|t=to come into being}}.<ref>{{R:grc:Beekes|576|ἴγνητες}}</ref>

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ɪɡˈneɪʃəs/}}
* {{hyph|en|Ig|na|tius}}

